  "local_port": 57242,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "To check your last three charges on your Vodafone account, you can use one of several convenient methods. The exact steps might vary slightly depending on your country and the specific Vodafone service you use, but generally, the following options are available:\n\n### 1. **Using the My Vodafone App**\n\n**a.** **Download and Install the App**:\n   - If you haven't already, download the **My Vodafone** app from the [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.vodafone.android) or [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/app/vodafone-my-vodafone/id332222308).\n\n**b.** **Log In to Your Account**:\n   - Open the app and sign in using your Vodafone account credentials (username and password). If you haven't set up an online account, you may need to register your mobile number and create a password.\n\n**c.** **Navigate to Billing or Account Section**:\n   - Once logged in, go to the **\"Billing\"**, **\"Account Details\"**, or a similarly named section.\n\n**d.** **View Recent Charges**:\n   - Here, you should see a list of your recent transactions or charges. Look for the last three entries to review your recent charges.\n\n### 2. **Via the Vodafone Website**\n\n**a.** **Visit the Official Vodafone Website**:\n   - Go to your local Vodafone website. For example, in the UK, it's [vodafone.co.uk](https://www.vodafone.co.uk/).\n\n**b.** **Log In to Your Account**:\n   - Click on the **\"My Vodafone\"** or **\"Login\"** button and enter your account credentials.\n\n**c.** **Access Your Billing Information**:\n   - Navigate to the **\"Billing\"**, **\"Account Summary\"**, or **\"Transactions\"** section.\n\n**d.** **Review Recent Charges**:\n   - Here, you'll find a detailed list of your recent charges. Look for the last three entries to review them.\n\n### 3. **Sending an SMS**\n\nVodafone often provides SMS services to check account details. The specific SMS command can vary by country, so here's a general approach:\n\n**a.** **Compose a New SMS**:\n   - Open your messaging app and create a new SMS.\n\n**b.** **Enter the Command**:\n   - Type a specific command provided by Vodafone to check your latest charges. Common commands include:\n     - `BAL` for balance\n     - `LAST3` or `RECENT` for recent charges\n   - **Note**: The exact command can vary, so it's best to check your local Vodafone website or contact customer service for the correct SMS command.\n\n**c.** **Send to the Designated Number**:\n   - Send the SMS to the Vodafone service number (often something like  *#123# or **221#).\n\n**d.** **Receive Your Charges**:\n   - You should receive a reply detailing your last three charges.\n\n### 4. **Calling Vodafone Customer Service**\n\nIf you prefer speaking directly with a representative:\n\n**a.** **Dial Vodafone Customer Support**:\n   - Find the customer service number for your country. Common numbers include:\n     - **UK**:  191 from a Vodafone mobile or 0333 304 0191 from any other phone.\n     - **Other Countries**: Visit your local Vodafone website to find the correct number.\n\n**b.** **Navigate the Automated Menu**:\n   - You might need to select options related to billing or account information.\n\n**c.** **Request Recent Charges**:\n   - Once connected to a representative, ask them to provide details of your last three charges.\n\n### 5. **Using Online Chat Support**\n\nMany Vodafone websites offer live chat support:\n\n**a.** **Visit the Vodafone Website**:\n   - Go to your local Vodafone website.\n\n**b.** **Access Live Chat**:\n   - Look for the **\"Contact Us\"**, **\"Support\"**, or **\"Live Chat\"** option.\n\n**c.** **Initiate a Chat Session**:\n   - Start a chat and authenticate your account if required.\n\n**d.** **Request Your Recent Charges**:\n   - Ask the support agent to provide details of your last three charges.\n\n---\n\n**Tips:**\n\n- **Ensure Security**: Always make sure you're accessing Vodafone services through official channels to protect your personal and financial information.\n  \n- **Account Registration**: If you haven't registered for online account management, consider doing so for easier access to your billing information.\n\n- **Check Local Vodafone Services**: Procedures can vary by country, so it's a good idea to refer to your local Vodafone website or contact local customer service for specific instructions.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need personalized assistance, contacting Vodafone customer support directly is the best course of action.",
